name: The Big Park
description:
That’s what we used to call this place when I was a kid, and nothing makes it feel bigger than the absence. I can still see so clearly in my mind’s eye the days of yelling “higher! higher!” on the swings as I reached for the limitless possibilities in the sky. Today, that feeling seems far out of reach.

3840x2160 JPEG

Photo by Jason Charnick
Taken in the Bronx, NY, USA
